    public class JobManagerCallbackAdapter

        public void onJobRun(Job job,
                     int resultCode)
        Description copied from interface: JobManagerCallback
        Called after a Job has been Run. Might be called multiple times if the Job runs multiple times (due to failures).
        Specified by:
        onJobRun in interface JobManagerCallback
        Parameters:
        job - The Job that did just run.
        resultCode - The result of the Job.onRun(). It is one of:

      • onDone

        public void onDone(Job job)
        Description copied from interface: JobManagerCallback
        Called after a Job is removed from the JobManager. It might be cancelled or onFinished. This call is a good place to be sure that JobManager is done with the Job.
        Specified by:
        onDone in interface JobManagerCallback

      • onAfterJobRun

        public void onAfterJobRun(Job job,
                          int resultCode)
        Description copied from interface: JobManagerCallback
        Called after a Job is run and its run result has been handled. For instance, if the Job is cancelled, this method is called after the job is removed from the queue.
        Specified by:
        onAfterJobRun in interface JobManagerCallback
        Parameters:
        job - The Job that just onFinished a run call.
        resultCode - The result of the run call.
